<table width="auto"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td colspan=3>House Bill/Resolution NO. <b>HB04696</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>FULL TITLE : AN ACT AMENDING SECTION 24 OF REPUBLIC ACT NO. 8424 OTHERWISE KNOWN AS "THE NATIONAL INTERNAL REVENUE CODE OF 1997" AS AMENDED, AND FOR OTHER PURPOSES</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SHORT TITLE : Tax Reform Act</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ABSTRACT : Seeks to adjust the levels of net taxable income with a simpler, standardized rates that is just and fair; Aims to restructure the income brackets and their corresponding tax rates, as well as align the maximum tax rate of corporate taxpayers; Proposes to establish an adjustment and index mechanism to reflect the fluctuating commodity market.</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PRINCIPAL AUTHOR/S : <b>VILLAFUERTE, LUIS RAYMUND JR. F.</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE FILED : 2016-12-15</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SIGNIFICANCE: NATIONAL</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>COMMITEE HEARINGS/ACTIONS:</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3><b>&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp1. Scheduled for meeting/hearing on 2017-05-10</b><tr><td colspan=3><b>&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp2. Approved by the Committee on Appropriations on 2017-05-10</b><tr><td colspan=3>&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp-Substitute Bill to House Bills Numbered 4774, 4688, 20, 35, 39, 57, 103, 137, 183, 292, 295, 333, 362, 363, 403, 411, 466, 562, 997, 1000, 1002, 1272, 1326, 1522, 1536, 1601, 1604, 1656, 1657, 1660, 1696, 1705, 1803, 1945, 1950, 2140, 2154, 2168, 2347, 2427, 2544, 2599, 2600, 2601, 3259, 3327, 3360, 3668, 3720, 3734, 3741, 4068, 4134, 4299 and 4696 was approved with amendments.</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>MOTHER BILL:&nbspHB05636</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE ON RULES</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>REFERRAL TO THE COMMITTEE ON WAYS AND MEANS ON 2017-01-16</td></tr></table>